sub_title: Innovation Manager at IDH. Deeply interested on smallholder farming systems and business models innovations as drivers of prosperity.
summary:
Interdisciplinary doctoral researcher in the Water Management department at Delft University of Technology. Currently exploring smallholders' adoption of sustainable irrigation technologies, and how innovative models can facilitate this process. Fond of Q methodology and its application across disciplines and cultures, particularly within challenges of the Global South. Work experience in Ecuador, Netherlands, Spain, Italy, Nepal, Indonesia and India.
At the moment in love with Sherpa/Himalayan cross-cultural mountaineering literature.
